  Title: God in All Worlds
  Locus:
    Page: 270
By: Pierre Teilhard de Chardin
---
In our approaches to woman, and when we come into contact with her, we are
enveloped in a sort of indistinct glow of illumination -- the instinctive
feeling that a new world awaits us and is about to develop in the depths of
matter -- if only we fold the wings of spirit, and surrender ourselves to
it. In our approaches to woman, and when we come into contact with her, we
are enveloped in a sort of indistinct glow of illumination -- the instinctive
feeling that a new world awaits us and is about to develop in the depths of
matter -- if only we fold the wings of spirit, and surrender ourselves to it.
